annotationA: Syntaxin 17, isoform B; Syntaxin 17 (Syx17) is a Qa type SNARE protein localizing to ER, mitochondria and autophagosomes. It mediates the fusion of autophagosomes with endosomes and lysosomes by forming a SNARE complex with Snap29 (Qbc) and Vamp7 (R). Syx17 roles include autophagosome clearance and neuromuscular function
annotationB: Secretory 22, isoform B; SNAP receptor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phagocytosis; retrograde vesicle-mediated transport, Golgi to ER; vesicle-mediated transport; ER to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport; vesicle fusion; Belongs to the synaptobrevin family
